parameters.name: AddressIpVersion
parameters.description:
The protocol. Valid values:

*   **IPv4** (default)
*   **DualStack**

>  An endpoint supports dual-stack if its associated endpoint service and VPC both support dual-stack.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the token, but you must make sure that the token is unique among different requests. The token can contain only ASCII characters.

parameters.name: DryRun
parameters.description:
Specifies whether to perform only a dry run, without performing the actual request. Valid values:

*   **true**: performs only a dry run. The system checks the request for potential issues, including missing parameter values, incorrect request syntax, and service limits. If the request fails the dry run, an error message is returned. If the request passes the dry run, the `DryRunOperation` error code is returned.
*   **false** (default): performs a dry run and performs the actual request. If the request passes the dry run, a 2xx HTTP status code is returned and the operation is performed.

parameters.name: EndpointDescription
parameters.description:
The description of the endpoint.

The description must be 2 to 256 characters in length, and cannot start with `http://` or `https://`.

parameters.name: EndpointName
parameters.description:
The name of the endpoint.

The name must be 2 to 128 characters in length, and can contain digits, underscores (\_), and hyphens (-). The name must start with a letter.

parameters.name: EndpointType
parameters.description:
The endpoint type. Valid values:

*   **Interface** You can specify an Application Load Balancer (ALB) instance, a Classic Load Balancer (CLB) instance, or a Network Load Balancer (NLB) instance.
*   **Reverse** You can specify a Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) NAT gateway.

>  Services that support reverse endpoints are provided by Alibaba Cloud or Alibaba Cloud partners. To create such a service on your own, contact your account manager.

parameters.name: ProtectedEnabled
parameters.description:
Specifies whether to enable user authentication. This parameter is available in Security Token Service (STS) mode. Valid values:

*   **true**: enables user authentication. After user authentication is enabled, only the user who creates the endpoint can modify or delete the endpoint in STS mode.
*   **false** (default): disables user authentication.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description:
The region ID of the endpoint.

You can call the [DescribeRegions](~~120468~~) operation to query the most recent region list.

parameters.name: SecurityGroupId
parameters.description: The IDs of security groups that are associated with the endpoint elastic network interface (ENI).

parameters.name: ServiceId
parameters.description: The ID of the endpoint service with which the endpoint is associated.

parameters.name: ServiceName
parameters.description: The name of the endpoint service with which the endpoint is associated.

parameters.name: Tag
parameters.description: The tags to add to the resource.

parameters.name: VpcId
parameters.description: The ID of the virtual private cloud (VPC) to which the endpoint belongs.

parameters.name: Zone
parameters.description: The zones where the endpoint is deployed.

parameters.name: ZonePrivateIpAddressCount
parameters.description: The number of private IP addresses that are assigned to an elastic network interface (ENI) in each zone. Set the value to **1**.
